metadata.name: Remainder #90
metadata.description:
Star maps, schematics, or just fragments of a memory … many things are lost to time, but these remain.
Each Remainder is composed entirely of points and lines generated from two randomly selected parametric equations involving the modulo operation, as a testament to the ancient and timeless beauty of mathematics. The equations are computed over variable sized grids and drawn in multiple layers, giving rise to a variety of shapes and texture. A GPU is required for rendering the output.

This artwork is interactive. Press [i] and [z] to reveal invisible ink and hidden layers. Try alternating the two keys to create your own unique output.
Press [s] to save the current view as an image.

Elsif 2022, made with p5js.

metadata.name: Memory Module #282
metadata.description:
Day by day, memories accumulate and shape our dreams, subconscious, ideals, and ultimately, the innermost self. 

This artwork is created by repeatedly drawing squares that are identical in size, with each one representing a memory. As new memories form, the older ones become obscured, fuzzy, or joined with others to form belief structures and intuitions. I hope that this work will remind you of someone, someplace, a song or a melody that’s important to you. 

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view in live mode.
[1] to [8] Change resolution, 1.5K to 12K.
[G] Toggle paper texture.

URL params:
aspect: custom aspect ratio (?aspect=3).
res: custom resolution multiplier (?res=4).

Made with fractal math and p5js, Memory Module is the first in a 5-part generative art series about introspection. You can read more about the series here: https://elsifthen.github.io/

Created by elsif, 2022.07.

metadata.name: Unstable Anticipation #52
metadata.description:
Minimal poster prints of blocks in motion.

Varying block arrangements fall from the canvas's top and interact with pegs near the bottom. After the animation completes, the scene is redrawn with a halftone pattern.

Matter JS is used to calculate the physics.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px

Features
* The length of the simulation
* Number, size, and position of the pegs
* Halftone grid size
* Varying amount of roughness for distorted halftone shapes
* Shape arrangement and composition
* 60/40% Color or monochrome

metadata.name: Learning to Fly #57
metadata.description:
It all started with @chilltulpa saying in fxhash discord "I wish i could make art" and @mknol answering with a few lines of code to create generative art... It was more than enough for me to finally dive in, and try to make something. 

Learning is the key here, learning is being alive.
This is me learning, this is a beginning, I'm learning to fly.

metadata.name: Digital Expression #56
metadata.description:
Digital Expression is a work of art that brings the power of simple geometric shapes, lines mix and reveal the power to generate complex, interesting and unexpected formations. All this visual versatility comes to life and a true Digital Expression that dialogues with everyone who views it.

Create with p5.js and p5.grain.

- Press "S" in live view mode after loading to save at 2000x2000px.
